#: ../../../user/building.rst:4
msgid "Building from source"
msgstr "從來源碼建置"

#: ../../../user/building.rst:6
msgid ""
"Building locally on your machine gives you complete control over build "
"options. If you are a MacOS or Linux user familiar with using the command "
"line, you can continue with building NumPy locally by following the "
"instructions below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/building.rst:11
msgid ""
"If you want to build NumPy for development purposes, please refer to :ref:"
"`development-environment` for additional information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/building.rst:19
msgid "Prerequisites"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/building.rst:21
msgid "Building NumPy requires the following software installed:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/building.rst:23
msgid "Python 3.9.x or newer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/building.rst:25
msgid ""
"Please note that the Python development headers also need to be installed, e."
"g., on Debian/Ubuntu one needs to install both `python3` and `python3-dev`. "
"On Windows and macOS this is normally not an issue."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/building.rst:29
msgid "Compilers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/building.rst:31
msgid ""
"Much of NumPy is written in C and C++.  You will need a C compiler that "
"complies with the C99 standard, and a C++ compiler that complies with the C+"
"+17 standard."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/building.rst:35
msgid ""
"While a FORTRAN 77 compiler is not necessary for building NumPy, it is "
"needed to run the ``numpy.f2py`` tests. These tests are skipped if the "
"compiler is not auto-detected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/building.rst:39
msgid ""
"Note that NumPy is developed mainly using GNU compilers and tested on MSVC "
"and Clang compilers. Compilers from other vendors such as Intel, Absoft, "
"Sun, NAG, Compaq, Vast, Portland, Lahey, HP, IBM are only supported in the "
"form of community feedback, and may not work out of the box.  GCC 6.5 (and "
"later) compilers are recommended. On ARM64 (aarch64) GCC 8.x (and later) are "
"recommended."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/building.rst:46
msgid "Linear Algebra libraries"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/building.rst:48
msgid ""
"NumPy does not require any external linear algebra libraries to be "
"installed. However, if these are available, NumPy's setup script can detect "
"them and use them for building. A number of different LAPACK library setups "
"can be used, including optimized LAPACK libraries such as OpenBLAS or MKL. "
"The choice and location of these libraries as well as include paths and "
"other such build options can be specified in a ``.pc`` file, as documented "
"in :ref:`scipy:building-blas-and-lapack`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/building.rst:56
msgid "Cython"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/building.rst:58
msgid "For building NumPy, you'll need a recent version of Cython."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/building.rst:60
msgid "The NumPy source code"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/building.rst:62
msgid "Clone the repository following the instructions in :doc:`/dev/index`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/building.rst:66
msgid ""
"Starting on version 1.26, NumPy will adopt Meson as its build system (see :"
"ref:`distutils-status-migration` and :doc:`scipy:building/"
"understanding_meson` for more details.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/building.rst:71
msgid "Basic installation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/building.rst:73
msgid "To build and install NumPy from a local copy of the source code, run::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/building.rst:75
msgid "pip install ."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/building.rst:77
msgid ""
"This will install all build dependencies and use Meson to compile and "
"install the NumPy C-extensions and Python modules. If you need more control "
"of build options and commands, see the following sections."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/building.rst:81
msgid ""
"To perform an in-place build that can be run from the source folder run::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/building.rst:83
msgid ""
"pip install -r build_requirements.txt\n"
"pip install -e . --no-build-isolation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/building.rst:86
msgid ""
"*Note: for build instructions to do development work on NumPy itself, see* :"
"ref:`development-environment`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/building.rst:91
msgid "Advanced building with Meson"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/building.rst:93
msgid ""
"Meson supports the standard environment variables ``CC``, ``CXX`` and ``FC`` "
"to select specific C, C++ and/or Fortran compilers. These environment "
"variables are documented in `the reference tables in the Meson docs <https://"
"mesonbuild.com/Reference-tables.html#compiler-and-linker-flag-environment-"
"variables>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/building.rst:98
msgid ""
"Note that environment variables only get applied from a clean build, because "
"they affect the configure stage (i.e., meson setup). An incremental rebuild "
"does not react to changes in environment variables - you have to run ``git "
"clean -xdf`` and do a full rebuild, or run ``meson setup --reconfigure``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/building.rst:103
msgid ""
"For more options including selecting compilers, setting custom compiler "
"flags and controlling parallelism, see :doc:`scipy:building/"
"compilers_and_options` (from the SciPy documentation) and `the Meson FAQ "
"<https://mesonbuild.com/howtox.html#set-extra-compiler-and-linker-flags-from-"
"the-outside-when-eg-building-distro-packages>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/building.rst:110
msgid "Testing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/building.rst:112
msgid ""
"Make sure to test your builds. To ensure everything stays in shape, see if "
"all tests pass."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/building.rst:115
msgid ""
"The test suite requires additional dependencies, which can easily be "
"installed with::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/building.rst:118
msgid "python -m pip install -r test_requirements.txt"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/building.rst:120
msgid "Run the full test suite with::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/building.rst:122
msgid ""
"cd ..  # avoid picking up the source tree\n"
"pytest --pyargs numpy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/building.rst:125
msgid "For detailed info on testing, see :ref:`testing-builds`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/building.rst:130
msgid "Accelerated BLAS/LAPACK libraries"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/building.rst:132
msgid ""
"NumPy searches for optimized linear algebra libraries such as BLAS and "
"LAPACK. There are specific orders for searching these libraries, as "
"described below and in the `meson_options.txt <https://github.com/numpy/"
"numpy/blob/main/meson_options.txt>`_ file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/building.rst:139
msgid "Cross compilation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/building.rst:141
msgid ""
"For cross compilation instructions, see :doc:`scipy:building/"
"cross_compilation` and the `Meson documentation <meson>`_."
msgstr ""
